President Obama spoke with Japanese Prime Minister Taro Aso to discuss the situation following North Korea's nuclear test. They both agreed that the test was a violation of United Nations Security Council Resolutions and called for a collective response from the international community. The leaders decided to intensify coordination with South Korea, China, and Russia, and pledged to work together in the United Nations Security Council to obtain a resolution with concrete measures to curb North Korea's nuclear and missile activities. President Obama also reiterated the United States' commitment to defending Japan and maintaining peace and security in Northeast Asia.